gomodel:SYNGO_5328  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 4: proximity labeling of synaptic cleft proteins identified NOTCH2.\n\nFigure 5e: NOTCH2 was also identified in western blots of synaptosome fractions prepared from adult rat brain.\n\nFigure 5g,h: immunofluorescence labeling of endogenous NOTCH2 showed partial localization apposed to Bassoon in both cultured cortical neurons and adult rat brain tissue.. Experimental description: species of the overexpressed protein is not listed, annotating against the identified protein in the proximity labeling assay.\n\n\"We therefore opted to use dissociated neuron culture, rather than intact brain tissue, to allow for rapid delivery and washout of biotin-phenol, H2O2, and subsequent peroxidase quenchers. At DIV19 (19 days in vitro), our embryonic rat cortical neuron cultures displayed abundant staining of synapse markers ...\"\n\nantibody:\nRabbit anti-Notch2, Abcam, Cat# ab8926 RRID: AB_2267338" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5328" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

